      • getEc2OnDemandPricing

        @Transactional(propagation=NOT_SUPPORTED)
public List<Ec2OnDemandPricing> getEc2OnDemandPricing(String ec2PricingListUrl)
        Retrieves EC2 on-demand pricing information from AWS.

        This implementation executes non-transactionally, suspends the current transaction if one exists.

        Specified by:
        getEc2OnDemandPricing in interface Ec2OnDemandPricingUpdateService
        Parameters:
        ec2PricingListUrl - the URL of the Amazon EC2 pricing list in JSON format
        Returns:
        the list of EC2 on-demand pricing entries

      • updateEc2OnDemandPricing

        @Transactional(propagation=REQUIRES_NEW)
public void updateEc2OnDemandPricing(List<Ec2OnDemandPricing> ec2OnDemandPricingEntries)
        Updates the EC2 on-demand pricing configured in the system per specified pricing information.

        This implementation starts a new transaction.

        Specified by:
        updateEc2OnDemandPricing in interface Ec2OnDemandPricingUpdateService
        Parameters:
        ec2OnDemandPricingEntries - the list of EC2 on-demand pricing entries

        protected Ec2OnDemandPricing createEc2OnDemandPricingEntry(String sku,
                                                           Object location,
                                                           Object operatingSystem,
                                                           Object instanceType,
                                                           Object tenancy,
                                                           Object usageType)
        Creates an EC2 on-demand pricing entry per specified parameters. This method returns null if input parameters fail validation.
        Parameters:
        sku - the SKU of the AWS product offering
        location - the AWS location information, maybe null
        operatingSystem - the operation system, maybe null
        instanceType - the EC2 instance type, maybe null
        tenancy - the EC2 tenancy, maybe null
        usageType - the usage type, maybe null
        Returns:
        the EC2 on-demand pricing or null if input parameters fail validation
